# Environment Variables

## Required for Production

### SignalR Service
- `SIGNALR_CONNECTION_STRING` — Azure SignalR Service connection string (from Azure Portal or Bicep outputs)
  - Format: `Endpoint=https://[name].service.signalr.net;AccessKey=[key];Version=1.0;`
  - Get from: `az deployment group show --name <deployment> --resource-group <rg> --query properties.outputs.signalRConnectionString.value -o tsv`

## Optional

### Server
- `PORT` — Server port (default: 3001)

## Development Mode

If `SIGNALR_CONNECTION_STRING` is not set, the server will automatically fall back to direct WebSocket connections for local development.
